the Federal Trade Commission (FTC), which maintains a database of complaints concerning identity theft; Â· the Social Security Administration's Office of the Inspector General (SSA/OIG), which operates a hotline to receive allegations of SSN misuse and program fraud; and Â· federal law enforcement agencies--Department of Justice components, Department of the Treasury components, and the Postal Inspection Service--responsible for investigating and prosecuting identity theftrelated cases.
