Also, in reference to table 8, EOUSA staff made the following clarifying comments: Â·
A given case may be counted under more than one of the three U.S. Code sections because a defendant could have been charged with multiple offenses.
However, in table 8's statistics for case filings, there is no double counting of multiple charges of the same Code section, nor of filings under the subsections of that section.
For instance, if a defendant was charged with two counts of violations under 18 U.S.C. Â§ 1028(a)(7) in one case, the relevant statistics would still appear as only one case under the 18 U.S.C. Â§ 1028 column in table 8.
