Of the top-issuing group of 14 banks, we were able to arrange in-person or telephone interviews with officials of 6 banks.
ABA, Deposit Account Fraud Survey Report 2000, p. 9.
ABA conducted its survey between February and June 2000 and received responses (completed survey forms) from 542 commercial banks.
According to the ABA, the reported loss figures represent extrapolations to the industry level.
ABA defined "loss avoidance" as the amount of losses avoided as a result of the banks' prevention systems and procedures.
